      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is an Interface?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "An interface in TypeScript defines the structure of an object, specifying the properties and their types."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "interface User {\n  name: string;\n  age: number;\n}\n\nlet user: User = {\n  name: 'John',\n  age: 30\n};"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Optional Properties"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "interface User {\n  name: string;\n  age?: number;\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Readonly Properties"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "interface User {\n  readonly id: number;\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Function Interface"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "interface AddFn {\n  (a: number, b: number): number;\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Extending Interfaces"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "interface Person {\n  name: string;\n}\n\ninterface Employee extends Person {\n  salary: number;\n}"
